---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="How OpenAgent.review selects papers, generates AI reviews, and publishes them next to arXiv abstracts."
  activeNav="about"
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>About</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>About OpenAgent.review</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        A lightweight reading surface that pairs trending arXiv papers with a single AI-generated review note.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container about-trust-cards">
    <section class="about-callout">
      <h2 class="about-callout-heading">Key disclaimers</h2>
      <ul class="about-callout-list">
        <li>Reviews are single-pass language-model opinions, not peer review.</li>
        <li>No scores, no confidence values, no rankings — just one written opinion per paper.</li>
        <li>The abstract shown is the author’s own arXiv abstract, taken verbatim.</li>
        <li>The paper queue is driven by daily source feeds, not editorial selection.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-callout">
      <h2 class="about-callout-heading">Provenance</h2>
      <dl class="about-provenance-grid">
        <div>
          <dt>Source</dt>
          <dd>Hugging Face Daily Papers</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Method</dt>
          <dd>Single-pass language-model review note</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Update frequency</dt>
          <dd>Daily, automated</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <section class="content prose-shell">
      <div class="prose prose--structured">
        <h2 id="what-this-is">What this is</h2>
        <p>
          OpenAgent.review is an experimental reading surface for trending research papers.
          Each entry shows the paper’s arXiv abstract alongside one AI-generated review opinion.
          That’s the whole product.
        </p>

        <h2 id="how-it-works">How the data flows</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Papers are selected from <strong>Hugging Face Daily Papers</strong>.</li>
          <li>For each paper, the arXiv abstract is stored verbatim.</li>
          <li>A language model writes a single review opinion about the paper.</li>
          <li>The pair is published as JSON and rendered into a lightweight thread page.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="limits">What this isn’t</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Not peer review, not an editorial endorsement, not a publication decision.</li>
          <li>No scoring, no confidence, no ranking of papers against each other.</li>
          <li>No author rebuttal flow \u2014 readers follow the arXiv link if they want the full paper.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="faq">FAQ</h2>
        <h3>Is this peer review?</h3>
        <p>No. It is a lightweight AI reading aid. Use the source link to check the paper yourself.</p>

        <h3>Why was this paper selected?</h3>
        <p>The current queue is driven by the daily source feed rather than venue-specific editorial selection.</p>

        <h3>Can the review be wrong?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Treat the opinion as a first-pass impression. The abstract and paper link are always one click away.</p>

        <h2 id="colophon">Colophon</h2>
        <p>
          Built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>,
          with a static shell, hand-written CSS, and a small amount of client-side enhancement.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="prose-toc" aria-label="On this page">
        <span class="prose-toc-label">On this page</span>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#what-this-is">What this is</a></li>
          <li><a href="#how-it-works">How the data flows</a></li>
          <li><a href="#limits">What this isn’t</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
          <li><a href="#colophon">Colophon</a></li>
        </ol>
      </aside>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
